==English==
===Etymology===
Uncertain; predates the [[Chadless punch]] (see [http://www.snopes.com/business/names/chad.asp the Snopes article on this supposed origin]; possibly from Scottish ''chad'', river [[gravel]], or the English slang term ''[[chat]]'', '''[[louse]]'''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æd|-æd]]

===Noun===
{{wikipediapar|Chad (paper)}}
'''chad''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''chads''')

#(''uncountable'') Small pieces of [[paper]] [[punch]]ed out from the [[edge]]s of [[continuous]] [[stationery]], [[punched card]]s, [[paper tape]] etc.
#(''countable'') One of these pieces of paper.

